{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01Kwy3pdZg2Mr1jfsXvEzWZF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals confirmed:\n\n- **app-producer**: `1/1 Running`, no more crash loop\n- **/app vhost**: `app-queue` exists, type `classic`, with 5 messages and growing\n- **Cluster**: 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) all running as disk nodes, healthy\n\n**Root cause**: the `app-user` had permissions on `/app` vhost of `configure=\"\"` (empty), `write=\".*\"`, `read=\".*\"` — the security tightening had stripped *configure* permission, so the user could publish/read but not declare (create) the queue, causing `not_authorised` on the producer's `PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` call.\n\n**Fix**: granted scoped `configure` permission limited to `app-` prefixed resources only (least-privilege, not a blanket `.*` grant):\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"^app-.*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThen restarted the `app-producer` deployment. No CRDs/operators used, no data touched/lost — only a permission grant was changed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1763,"cache_read_input_tokens":44696,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1763},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f162e166-7ebd-4407-933d-e071e155dfcc","uuid":"2c36ad60-0f00-483d-9932-02dec80abbd7","request_id":"req_011CcamrSJqk2LVkfpNzaN6M"}
